text: Calvin Wray Lawrence House is a historic home located near Apex, Wake County, North Carolina. The house was built about 1890, and is a two-story, three-bay, single-pile frame I-house with a central hall plan. It has a triple-A-roof; full-width, hip-roof front porch; and a two-story addition and two-story gabled rear ell. Also on the property are the contributing well house, outhouse, and storage barn. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2008. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in North Carolina Category:Houses completed in 1890 Category:Houses in Wake County, North Carolina Category:National Register of Historic Places in Wake County, North Carolina
